ing of self-generated emotions|journal=Nature Neuroscience | volume = 3|pages=1049\u20131056|year=2000|vauthors=Damasio AR, Grabowski TJ, Bechara A, Damasio H, Ponto LL, Parvizi J, Hichwa RD |doi=10.1038/79871|pmid=11017179|issue=10|url=https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/a1b487f1009a065b305eb22cf30f75eda5a15af6 }}\n* {{cite journal |title=How the brain creates the mind|journal=Scientific American | volume = 281|pages=74\u201379|year=1999|author= Damasio AR. |doi=10.1038/scientificamerican1299-112 |pmid=10614073 |issue=6|bibcode=1999SciAm.281f.112D }}\n* {{cite journal|title=Investigating the biology of consciousness |journal= Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London. Series B: Biological Sciences| volume = 353|issue=1377 |pages=1879\u20131882|year=1998|author= Damasio AR|doi=10.1098/rstb.1998.0339|pmid=9854259 |pmc=1692416}}\n* {{cite journal|title=Deciding advantageously before knowing the advantageous strategy|journal=Science | volume = 275|pages=1293\u20131294|year=1997|vauthors=Bechara A, Damasio H, Tranel D, Damasio AR |doi=10.1126/science.275.5304.1293|issue=5304|pmid=9036851}}\n* {{cite journal|title=The somatic marker hypothesis and the possible functions of the prefrontal cortex|journal=Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London. Series B: Biological Sciences| volume =  351|pages=1413\u20131420|year=1996|author= Damasio AR.|doi=10.1098/rstb.1996.0125|pmid=8941953|issue=1346}}\n* {{cite journal|title=Insensitivity to future consequences following damage to human prefrontal cortex|journal=Cognition |pages=7\u201315|year=1994|vauthors=Bechara A, Damasio AR, Damasio H, Anderson S |doi=10.1016/0010-0277(94)90018-3|volume=50|pmid=8039375|issue=1\u20133|url=https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/ac44c0f20422c96ba09910aabc064ee4a9d2aaef }}\n* {{cite journal|title=Impaired recognition of emotion in facial expressions following bilateral damage to the human amygdala|journal=Nature | volume = 372|pages=669\u2013672|year=1994|vauthors=